HEADWORD: Lutzen
<hw>Lutzen</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A battle in the Thirty Years' War
(1632) at which the Swedes under King Gustavus Adolphus defeated the
Imperialists under Wallenstein, and in which Adolphus was
killed.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> battle of Lutzen.</syn>⟦br⟧
